				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				&lt;Simple: Cosmetic changes to the game &lt;interface/mechanics are totally OOC. In RP &lt;terms, nothing was changed on my character. Or &lt;did you RP your character as looking like an &lt;oragami figure before Luclin? <BR>
<BR>
no but roleplaying doesnt mean that you play a matrix full of attribute numbers or stats, roleplaying means, you make your avatar, you choose your appearance, (at tabletop you also describe how do you look like so everybody can imagine your roleplaying persona) with which you can identify, and the stats are just numerical description of your skills and abilities.<BR>
<BR>
when you start roleplaying, you dont say: My 23lv human female roque with stats 150 str 100 agi skill dagger lv130 enters the inn, but you say, I enter the in, i am tall with red long hair, green eyes, i look rather cute so most of the people think i am just some village maid in trousers, i wear whats ever, only the sharp dagger looking from my pocket shows, that may be it is not that safe to argue with me.<BR>
<BR>
you do imagine allways how your avatar does look alike, and in 3d game you choose the face and body and race you like to represent your avatar. dont tell me you didnt click through all the face choises when you made your characters, and that you didnt try to get gear that fits to your feeling how the character should look?<BR>
<BR>
so any cosmeticaly change on character that you dont want is a huge encroachment to you character identity you have build up.<BR>
<BR>
when i talk to people who have the SOL modells on, they just dont see me, or my character, they see some cartoony ugly long nosed elfen female with huge hunchbacks on  both side of her breastplate, thats deffinetely not my character i have chosen, that i was playing. i cannot smile or dance, cause they see not my character, my character is the original elf, with her cute movements and realy nice looking face and proportional siliconless body.<BR>
<BR>
even when you play text muds you describe yourself to other players, so you are something special.<BR>
<BR>
the new modells have for all elves (half, wood high and dark) one basic face, which has then very little modifications, so there are running now thousands of similar looking elfs, only on dark elven one they tried to make them a little feminin. <BR>
<BR>
they screwed up the erudites so, that there are very few of them except for people who play with old modells or dont have the expansion.<BR>
<BR>
bah
